This paper is about improving the efficiency of image retrieval using a novel diffusion technique. The paper discusses the use of diffusion as a ranking or re-ranking method in retrieval tasks, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper specifically focuses on image retrieval, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves pre-computing diffusion results for each element in the database, which can be seen as a form of offline processing. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the computational cost of the proposed method, which implies that it may also be relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
